  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_0' aria-label=\" Vinay Aggarwal versus The State of Haryana and Ors. pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('0','2025','2025_4_497_503','2025INSC433'); ><font size='4'> <strong>VINAY AGGARWAL<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>THE STATE OF HARYANA AND ORS. </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 4 S.C.R. 497</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 433</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010001192025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : SUDHANSHU DHULIA<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, K. VINOD CHANDRAN</strong><br> Issue for Consideration In the instant case, the Single Judge of the High Court directed that the investigation be handed over to CBI. Whether the order of the Single Judge of the High Court is sustainable. Headnotes&dagger; Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 &ndash; s.482 &ndash; The appellant was registered u/ss.120B, 177, 406, 420, 467, 468, 471, 506 of IPC &ndash; The complainant then filed a petition u/s.482 of the CrPC and sought transfer of investigation from the civil police of the State of Haryana to the CBI &ndash; The said petition was allowed by the High Court &ndash;<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 01-04-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CRIMINAL APPEAL No. 1744/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Appeal(s) allowed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('0','2025','2025_4_497_503','2025INSC433','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='co